1
00:00:00,410 --> 00:00:02,040
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:03,680
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:08,010 --> 00:00:10,010
(Episode 7)

4
00:00:28,370 --> 00:00:29,730
But I'm full.

5
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:34,640
See you later.

6
00:00:48,150 --> 00:00:50,760
Did you know
your wife is cheating on you?

7
00:00:51,720 --> 00:00:55,130
It looks like she left with a man.

8
00:00:59,160 --> 00:01:01,500
She completely stole my heart...

9
00:01:03,770 --> 00:01:05,970
and acted like
she'd love me forever.

10
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:08,270
- She could've at least said bye.
- Don't look.

11
00:01:09,610 --> 00:01:12,110
Then all of a sudden, poof.

12
00:01:12,740 --> 00:01:16,750
If she just up and runs away...

13
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:19,820
How could she do that?

14
00:01:36,570 --> 00:01:40,570
- What are you talking about?
- Hui Gyeong cheated on me.

15
00:01:41,540 --> 00:01:43,480
She had an affair
and ran off behind my back.

16
00:01:44,740 --> 00:01:45,910
She was cheating on me.

17
00:01:46,610 --> 00:01:49,280
She just up and left.
Just like my father...

18
00:01:49,750 --> 00:01:51,550
- She just...
- Dae Han.

19
00:01:54,890 --> 00:01:56,420
Seong Mi, wait. Seong Mi...

20
00:01:57,220 --> 00:01:58,220
I have a favor to ask.

21
00:01:59,890 --> 00:02:03,630
Promise not to tell Mom
and Jeong Han. Okay?

22
00:02:03,730 --> 00:02:06,100
If Mom and Jeong Han find out,
they'll be heartbroken...

23
00:02:09,430 --> 00:02:12,770
Mom might collapse again,
so please just keep it a secret.

24
00:02:14,010 --> 00:02:15,310
Collapse over what?

25
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:26,180
- Mother.
- Mom.

26
00:02:26,250 --> 00:02:27,720
Collapse?
Why on earth would I collapse?

27
00:02:28,090 --> 00:02:31,190
In your eyes,
do I really seem that weak?

28
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:36,160
Mom.

29
00:02:40,060 --> 00:02:41,870
- Mom...
- Oh, my.

30
00:02:41,930 --> 00:02:43,670
- Dae Han.
- Dae Han!

31
00:02:43,870 --> 00:02:45,470
- Dae Han.
- Dae Han, are you okay?

32
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:46,970
- Mom, I was so...
- Dae Han.

33
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:49,040
- Hey.
- I'm sorry, Mom...

34
00:02:49,310 --> 00:02:51,510
- Dae Han.
- I'm sorry.

35
00:02:51,580 --> 00:02:54,010
- My gosh. Dae Han.
- Mom, Grandma.

36
00:02:54,810 --> 00:02:55,810
What's wrong with Uncle?

37
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:58,080
- Woo Jae, help me with him.
- Yes, let me...

38
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:59,380
- I'm sorry, Mom.
- Here.

39
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:00,520
Hold him up.

40
00:03:00,790 --> 00:03:02,290
I'm sorry, Mom.

41
00:03:02,650 --> 00:03:04,760
- Here, careful.
- I'm sorry.

42
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:07,060
I'm sorry.

43
00:03:07,790 --> 00:03:11,260
- I'm sorry, Mom.
- Mom, what's wrong with Uncle?

44
00:03:12,230 --> 00:03:13,770
I'm sorry, Mom!

45
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:19,800
Uncle, how did you get this drunk?

46
00:03:20,410 --> 00:03:21,410
Woo Jae.

47
00:03:22,810 --> 00:03:25,180
Sorry, your uncle is such a fool.

48
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:29,380
Seong Mi, Mom... I'm sorry.

49
00:03:30,650 --> 00:03:32,750
It's all my fault
that Hui Gyeong ran away.

50
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,350
What... What's he saying?

51
00:03:36,690 --> 00:03:37,720
Let's step out, okay?

52
00:03:47,170 --> 00:03:48,170
Mom.

53
00:03:54,810 --> 00:03:55,810
Yes.

54
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,610
I'm your mother.

55
00:03:58,740 --> 00:04:02,110
When things are this hard,
you should've come to me first.

56
00:04:02,850 --> 00:04:05,180
Why are you facing this alone? Why?

57
00:04:05,420 --> 00:04:07,520
Why are you hurting all by yourself?
Why?

58
00:04:08,150 --> 00:04:09,150
Mom.

59
00:04:10,020 --> 00:04:11,160
What do I do?

60
00:04:13,930 --> 00:04:15,060
What do I do?

61
00:04:19,900 --> 00:04:21,170
Mom, what am I going to do?

62
00:04:21,930 --> 00:04:23,000
What do I do?

63
00:04:29,210 --> 00:04:30,240
It's okay.

64
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:34,580
It's going to be okay.

65
00:04:36,050 --> 00:04:37,080
Mom.

66
00:04:37,950 --> 00:04:40,390
What do I do, Mom?

67
00:04:48,890 --> 00:04:52,130
I don't get it.
She was packing to move yesterday.

68
00:04:52,730 --> 00:04:55,700
How did Aunt Hui Gyeong run away?
What's going on?

69
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:57,600
I'm not really sure either.

70
00:04:59,970 --> 00:05:01,740
Grandma must be so devastated.

71
00:05:02,540 --> 00:05:04,410
Grandfather left the same way,
you know.

72
00:05:05,580 --> 00:05:07,550
I know. If your dad finds out,

73
00:05:07,550 --> 00:05:09,280
it'll be hard.
It'll bring up the past.

74
00:05:10,380 --> 00:05:12,020
I'll just pretend
I didn't hear anything.

75
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:13,850
Okay. Go on upstairs.

76
00:05:17,660 --> 00:05:19,590
- Good night, Grandma.
- Okay, you too.

77
00:05:21,290 --> 00:05:23,030
Just leave him be. He'll be okay.

78
00:05:23,930 --> 00:05:24,930
Okay, Mother.

79
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,870
What could Dae Han have done wrong?

80
00:05:32,570 --> 00:05:33,570
Or was it...

81
00:05:34,670 --> 00:05:36,340
something I did? Did I upset her?

82
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:39,980
No.

83
00:05:40,510 --> 00:05:43,350
Of course not.
Don't even think that, Mother.

84
00:05:45,580 --> 00:05:46,580
Oh, dear.

85
00:05:48,620 --> 00:05:52,020
I never thought I'd live
to see a day like this again.

86
00:05:54,290 --> 00:05:55,930
I'll try and take care of it.

87
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:59,430
Don't be silly.
You're too busy for that.

88
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:04,240
- Forget it.
- I can't let her get away with it.

89
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:10,410
I'll find her, get the story,
get our money and an apology.

90
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:12,480
It's the only way
we can all move on.

91
00:06:14,510 --> 00:06:17,150
- I'm home.
- You're back?

92
00:06:17,220 --> 00:06:21,590
Is Dae Han back?
Mom, how's Hui Gyeong's aunt?

93
00:06:21,790 --> 00:06:23,150
Your brother's asleep,

94
00:06:23,150 --> 00:06:25,860
- and they said her aunt is fine.
- I see.

95
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,960
You two go on in.
I'll head to bed soon, too.

96
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:31,530
But wait, Mom, you look upset.
Is something wrong?

97
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:34,400
Hey, come on. Let's go to our room.
Good night, Mother.

98
00:06:34,470 --> 00:06:35,900
Go on. Let's go.

99
00:06:41,740 --> 00:06:44,140
Let's postpone next week's filming.

100
00:06:44,510 --> 00:06:47,010
- Why?
- Something came up at home.

101
00:06:47,180 --> 00:06:48,180
Something at home?

102
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:49,980
Why? What's going on at home?

103
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:52,250
With your family, that is.

104
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:55,450
What is it?
Is there something I don't know?

105
00:06:55,850 --> 00:06:58,320
Of course, there is.
There always is.

106
00:06:59,660 --> 00:07:02,890
You're not interested anyway,
so I'll just handle it myself.

107
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:07,630
So just stay out of it
and focus on your work like always.

108
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,400
I'm calling Director Song, okay?

109
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:14,710
Hold on, just sit down.
I have a really funny story for you.

110
00:07:14,770 --> 00:07:17,040
Forget it. I'm not in the mood.

111
00:07:17,380 --> 00:07:21,650
No, but you have to hear this.
Bucket was so funny today.

112
00:07:21,710 --> 00:07:24,580
I was laughing so hard
I almost died.

113
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:28,020
Why? What did he do this time?

114
00:07:28,090 --> 00:07:32,090
Get this. The guy who begged me
on his knees to be Vice President...

115
00:07:32,290 --> 00:07:34,690
is already skipping
morning workouts,

116
00:07:34,690 --> 00:07:36,260
claiming he's sick.

117
00:07:36,590 --> 00:07:41,070
So I sent him
that video of him kneeling.

118
00:07:41,430 --> 00:07:43,530
And he came running
like his life depended on it.

119
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:46,800
- It was priceless!
- You recorded it?

120
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:49,710
No, from the security camera
at the clinic.

121
00:07:49,710 --> 00:07:53,080
- I downloaded the footage.
- That guy is something else.

122
00:07:53,140 --> 00:07:56,680
And that's not all. Check this out.

123
00:07:57,180 --> 00:08:00,120
Here are the accounting ledgers
for the past three years...

124
00:08:00,180 --> 00:08:04,090
and the event summary reports.
Organize them by category.

125
00:08:04,890 --> 00:08:08,090
- Right now?
- Yes. When you're done with that,

126
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:11,630
run the night market survey.
Get it done this week.

127
00:08:12,060 --> 00:08:13,200
By the end of this week?

128
00:08:13,330 --> 00:08:18,040
Right. And you need to fill out
a daily work log,

129
00:08:18,140 --> 00:08:21,240
report it to me,
and then you can clock out.

130
00:08:21,540 --> 00:08:24,380
A work log?
Why can't I just tell you...

131
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:28,380
That's not going to work.
It's important to keep a record.

132
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:36,020
Yes, sir.

133
00:08:36,020 --> 00:08:37,460
(Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association)

134
00:08:37,460 --> 00:08:38,460
Pardon?

135
00:08:38,760 --> 00:08:41,030
The toilet in Building A's restroom
is clogged?

136
00:08:41,290 --> 00:08:44,960
That's a problem.
The maintenance staff have all left.

137
00:08:45,030 --> 00:08:46,530
So there's no one here right now.

138
00:08:47,470 --> 00:08:50,200
I guess I'll have to do it myself...

139
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:55,970
Wait. I've got someone right here.
Right, yes.

140
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:58,480
Yes. I'll send someone right over.

141
00:08:59,140 --> 00:09:00,880
Don't mention it.

142
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:03,280
Just doing my job as president.
All right.

143
00:09:05,180 --> 00:09:06,180
You heard that, right?

144
00:09:06,780 --> 00:09:08,490
Building A's restroom.

145
00:09:09,090 --> 00:09:10,150
So what?

146
00:09:10,660 --> 00:09:11,660
Go unclog it.

147
00:09:12,460 --> 00:09:16,060
Hey! These are a doctor's hands,
meant for taking pulses.

148
00:09:16,130 --> 00:09:19,730
I was awarded "Golden Hands"
at the Korean medicine conference!

149
00:09:19,860 --> 00:09:22,870
Goodness. There's a title
for everything, isn't there?

150
00:09:23,170 --> 00:09:27,910
Who told you to use your bare hands?
That's what tools are for.

151
00:09:28,070 --> 00:09:31,240
Come on,
you know I have a weak stomach.

152
00:09:31,310 --> 00:09:33,310
I know. I hear
you can't use public toilets...

153
00:09:33,380 --> 00:09:35,110
and have to run home
just to use the bathroom.

154
00:09:35,210 --> 00:09:36,710
You know that,
and you still want me to unclog it?

155
00:09:37,580 --> 00:09:40,690
Fine, if you don't want to,
you don't have to.

156
00:09:41,350 --> 00:09:42,820
Now, where did I put that video?

157
00:09:44,190 --> 00:09:45,790
Hey, you petty jerk.

158
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:48,260
This is so low and dirty.
Fine, I'll do it...

159
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:54,370
Hey, make sure you get that thing
good and clear, okay?

160
00:09:57,940 --> 00:10:01,570
So? Don't tell me you quit
just because you felt...

161
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:02,940
it was gross and beneath you.

162
00:10:03,610 --> 00:10:04,610
No.

163
00:10:18,420 --> 00:10:21,490
Gosh, really.
Dr. Gong is going way too far.

164
00:10:22,530 --> 00:10:24,400
That jerk humiliated me.

165
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:33,670
Should I really...

166
00:10:34,370 --> 00:10:35,910
keep putting up
with this humiliation?

167
00:10:36,070 --> 00:10:39,040
Of course.
This is all for your own good,

168
00:10:39,110 --> 00:10:40,340
so you have to endure it.

169
00:10:40,610 --> 00:10:42,380
How is any of this for me?

170
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:44,280
Look, honey.

171
00:10:45,050 --> 00:10:48,520
Your valuable labor
got that toilet unclogged, right?

172
00:10:48,590 --> 00:10:50,960
You solved someone's problem,

173
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:52,690
and their gratitude
will eventually...

174
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:54,860
turn into another vote
in your favor.

175
00:10:55,790 --> 00:10:58,630
All this humiliation
just for one lousy vote?

176
00:10:58,730 --> 00:11:02,900
We learned the hard way
how precious one vote is, honey.

177
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:04,570
Back then...

178
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,840
If only we'd gotten one more vote...

179
00:11:08,070 --> 00:11:10,540
Honey, I heard Mr. Hwang...

180
00:11:10,610 --> 00:11:12,910
was thrilled about you
becoming the Vice President.

181
00:11:13,140 --> 00:11:17,720
Let's get some sun and enjoy
a round of golf this weekend, okay?

182
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:22,190
Come on, go get cleaned up.

183
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:24,790
I'll even put your body lotion on
for you tonight.

184
00:11:25,820 --> 00:11:26,890
I love you.

185
00:11:27,890 --> 00:11:30,290
Hurry. Go on now.

186
00:11:31,030 --> 00:11:32,530
You think
that'll get rid of the smell?

187
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:37,470
Auntie!

188
00:11:39,170 --> 00:11:40,240
Oh, boy...

189
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:42,840
He's not there.

190
00:11:43,170 --> 00:11:45,710
Not at the gaming cafe,
not at the pool hall,

191
00:11:46,540 --> 00:11:51,180
- or the sauna, Ji Hu.
- Hey, Dong Suk.

192
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:53,720
Ji Hu, could you give us a minute?

193
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:57,220
It's okay. I know what's going on.

194
00:11:58,260 --> 00:12:00,220
My dad took your things, didn't he?

195
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:02,490
You think that's all he did?

196
00:12:03,590 --> 00:12:08,070
He stole everything from the store
where he worked, too.

197
00:12:09,170 --> 00:12:11,500
He even cleaned out
the bank account...

198
00:12:11,570 --> 00:12:14,340
where he was saving his paychecks
and disappeared.

199
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:26,150
This is juicy! I must tell Grandpa.

200
00:12:26,780 --> 00:12:28,750
- Yang Eun Bin!
- What?

201
00:12:29,490 --> 00:12:32,160
If Grandfather finds out about this,
he'll call the police.

202
00:12:32,220 --> 00:12:34,760
- Of course, he should. Grandpa...
- Come here.

203
00:12:34,890 --> 00:12:38,430
Hey! If the neighborhood finds out,

204
00:12:38,430 --> 00:12:39,530
it'll be a disgrace to our family!

205
00:12:39,930 --> 00:12:43,070
The market gossip can be so vicious.
Forget about your dad's future.

206
00:12:43,130 --> 00:12:45,340
It could reflect badly on you
and your brother, too.

207
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:51,340
I'm going to handle this quietly.
Nod if you understand.

208
00:12:56,280 --> 00:12:59,520
Don't you forget
that this is a secret.

209
00:13:00,820 --> 00:13:02,620
Then get me a spa membership!

210
00:13:04,050 --> 00:13:06,120
- Deal!
- Sweet!

211
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:21,440
Yes.

212
00:13:22,540 --> 00:13:26,940
Are you done yet? They say to hurry.
We're going to get some good food.

213
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:31,350
I'm not sure if I should use this
for my presentation.

214
00:13:34,220 --> 00:13:36,520
What's wrong now? What?
Is it something about the Director?

215
00:13:36,890 --> 00:13:37,890
Yes.

216
00:13:38,820 --> 00:13:42,390
If I use this,
he'll figure out that I know...

217
00:13:42,460 --> 00:13:45,360
that he's Yang Hyun Bin.

218
00:13:47,260 --> 00:13:51,700
Isn't it time he knew you know?
Please, just tell him already.

219
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:54,710
How can I?
The Vice President is even here.

220
00:14:01,580 --> 00:14:03,650
(Seohae Garden)

221
00:14:04,950 --> 00:14:07,820
I wonder why the Vice President
and the Director aren't coming in.

222
00:14:08,120 --> 00:14:09,750
You don't think they're fighting,
do you?

223
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:14,020
- This is all your fault.
- I know.

224
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:18,830
- I'm the traitor, the spy. Happy?
- Jerk...

225
00:14:23,130 --> 00:14:24,130
Hey.

226
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:28,740
The Director might dump the VP
and switch over to you.

227
00:14:29,110 --> 00:14:32,580
Gosh, you really need to stop
watching those dating shows.

228
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:37,620
Come on, it's not like the VP
isn't allowed to be here.

229
00:14:43,390 --> 00:14:46,920
If you barge in and ignore my plans,
where does that leave me?

230
00:14:48,230 --> 00:14:51,760
Is treating the employees to a meal
really worth getting so angry about?

231
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:55,270
And you're making them suffer
just to copy some reality show.

232
00:14:55,330 --> 00:14:59,040
No! This is how they earn a reward
and pride that money can't buy. See?

233
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:01,740
That's the priceless experience
I'm trying to give them.

234
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:05,210
As Vice President,
I'm also looking out for the staff.

235
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:07,110
That is a bold-faced lie.

236
00:15:08,410 --> 00:15:10,650
Just be honest with me,
and I'll forgive you.

237
00:15:15,390 --> 00:15:17,590
The company is suffocating me,

238
00:15:17,590 --> 00:15:19,620
and caring for my father
is too much.

239
00:15:19,990 --> 00:15:22,360
I can't do anything I want,
let alone have a relationship.

240
00:15:22,990 --> 00:15:23,990
But...

241
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:27,930
watching you and Ms. Gong Ju Ah
is so exciting and fun,

242
00:15:28,930 --> 00:15:30,470
so I came here to live vicariously
through you two.

243
00:15:37,510 --> 00:15:40,040
Fine. Then you only get to watch.

244
00:15:41,450 --> 00:15:45,020
But you have to tell her
you're Yang Hyun Bin today.

245
00:15:45,620 --> 00:15:47,150
Or I'll tell her myself.

246
00:15:54,460 --> 00:15:55,530
Unbelievable.

247
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:02,900
Please, eat!
You must all be starving.

248
00:16:03,770 --> 00:16:06,240
- Thank you for the food.
- Enjoy your meal.

249
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:07,640
So...

250
00:16:09,310 --> 00:16:10,870
Am I making everyone uncomfortable?

251
00:16:12,010 --> 00:16:13,510
- No, not at all.
- Of course not.

252
00:16:13,580 --> 00:16:14,580
Not at all!

253
00:16:14,650 --> 00:16:17,380
Not at all. You came all this way
and are even buying us dinner.

254
00:16:17,380 --> 00:16:18,950
We're incredibly grateful.

255
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:21,590
Thank you. I'm glad you understand,
Mr. Park.

256
00:16:22,490 --> 00:16:25,790
- Everyone, dig in.
- Enjoy your meal.

257
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:30,730
As you all know,
our Taehan Group began in fashion.

258
00:16:31,760 --> 00:16:36,070
The Chairman has a soft spot
for the Fashion Division.

259
00:16:36,630 --> 00:16:39,600
So I need you all
to win this competition...

260
00:16:40,070 --> 00:16:43,170
and prove your talent
and your worth!

261
00:16:43,240 --> 00:16:44,880
- We'll do our best!
- Yes.

262
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:46,580
- Enjoy your meal.
- Enjoy your meal.

263
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:48,180
- Thanks for the food.
- Enjoy your meal.

264
00:16:48,250 --> 00:16:52,180
The Chairman says our designers
illuminate our company's future...

265
00:16:52,250 --> 00:16:53,650
Give it a rest!

266
00:16:54,390 --> 00:16:55,490
Oh, right.

267
00:16:55,790 --> 00:16:57,590
Sorry. I'm sorry.

268
00:16:58,790 --> 00:16:59,790
Goodness...

269
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:03,290
- Eat up. Please, eat.
- Yes, let's eat.

270
00:17:04,360 --> 00:17:06,660
- Yes, thank you for the food.
- Yes, enjoy.

271
00:17:08,370 --> 00:17:10,030
I told you not to be so obvious,
didn't I?

272
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:13,900
- What? I didn't do anything.
- Whatever! Just hurry up and eat.

273
00:17:14,510 --> 00:17:15,940
Pacu Nacho.

274
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:33,190
Looking at you up close...

275
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:36,530
You kind of look like an anteater.

276
00:17:38,530 --> 00:17:40,500
You look like a sunfish.

277
00:17:41,430 --> 00:17:42,830
Hey, sunfish are cute.

278
00:17:43,870 --> 00:17:47,240
- Sure.
- Seriously. You just wait.

279
00:18:34,650 --> 00:18:35,820
It's a good thing I came.
Without me,

280
00:18:35,820 --> 00:18:36,920
the pairs would've been uneven,
right?

281
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:40,790
You're right. It's an honor
to have you draw me, Vice President.

282
00:18:44,460 --> 00:18:45,900
Don't get your hopes up.

283
00:18:48,230 --> 00:18:50,130
What's the point of this, Director?

284
00:18:51,030 --> 00:18:52,140
This is...

285
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:56,940
To observe each other's faces
to bridge the psychological gap...

286
00:18:57,040 --> 00:19:01,080
and communicate without words.
That's the purpose, Vice President.

287
00:19:02,280 --> 00:19:06,150
After this,
we'll discuss the first creation,

288
00:19:06,220 --> 00:19:09,450
and we'll share our motivations
to build a sense of unity.

289
00:19:09,820 --> 00:19:11,620
No interruptions are allowed.
Got it?

290
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:13,990
That sounds boring.

291
00:19:15,760 --> 00:19:17,490
Maybe we should have switched
your partners.

292
00:19:18,430 --> 00:19:21,870
- Why is that?
- Since you two are a couple...

293
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:23,730
- Come on!
- My gosh!

294
00:19:24,230 --> 00:19:26,770
Pacu Nacho and I are just friends.
That's all.

295
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:28,040
Really?

296
00:19:28,040 --> 00:19:30,540
The rumor going around the office
is that you two are a couple.

297
00:19:30,610 --> 00:19:33,880
The VP has a sick sense of humor,
lying to the executives.

298
00:19:34,480 --> 00:19:35,480
Ms. Gong Ju Ah.

299
00:19:36,010 --> 00:19:37,310
Do you have a boyfriend,
by any chance?

300
00:19:37,750 --> 00:19:39,650
Excuse me, VP.
We're here for the workshop.

301
00:19:39,650 --> 00:19:41,590
- Please save personal questions...
- She doesn't have one.

302
00:19:41,950 --> 00:19:43,050
About three years ago, I think?

303
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:45,690
Her last one lasted
about 7 to 8 months.

304
00:19:45,790 --> 00:19:47,360
- What are you doing?
- What?

305
00:19:50,260 --> 00:19:53,400
Come to think of it,
why isn't our Pacu Nacho dating?

306
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:56,130
Now that I think about it,
he never dated in Argentina either.

307
00:19:57,230 --> 00:20:00,400
Is there an unforgettable first love
you're hung up on?

308
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:05,380
Maybe a girl you liked
before you went abroad?

309
00:20:06,740 --> 00:20:07,780
Right, Ms. Gong?

310
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:13,920
Shoot!
How did my eraser fly over there?

311
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:16,120
How weird.

312
00:20:21,860 --> 00:20:22,860
Weird indeed.

313
00:20:27,730 --> 00:20:28,770
When I was in elementary school,

314
00:20:29,230 --> 00:20:31,800
I made this apron for my mom,
who used to run a restaurant.

315
00:20:33,270 --> 00:20:36,440
When the nearby shop owners saw it,
they placed orders too,

316
00:20:37,740 --> 00:20:39,810
and as I kept making things,

317
00:20:41,510 --> 00:20:43,050
I ended up becoming the designer,
Jo Seong Min.

318
00:20:45,850 --> 00:20:47,520
This scarf was...

319
00:20:47,520 --> 00:20:49,890
the first birthday gift
I ever gave my dad.

320
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:57,060
This is an outfit
I made for my dog, Gamja.

321
00:20:57,730 --> 00:21:01,130
Gamja passed away a while ago,

322
00:21:03,330 --> 00:21:04,970
but she'll forever be my muse.

323
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:09,840
I was born and raised
without a father.

324
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:12,340
To this day,
I still don't know who he is.

325
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:16,580
What some might call
a child born out of wedlock.

326
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:19,620
When I was in high school,

327
00:21:20,750 --> 00:21:24,620
I didn't know what to do in life,
so I was lost for a while.

328
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:29,030
But then,
my mother told me something.

329
00:21:29,630 --> 00:21:31,900
She said my father had been
a clothing designer.

330
00:21:33,060 --> 00:21:36,100
So I started studying hard
and made this. And with it,

331
00:21:36,770 --> 00:21:39,540
I won the Taehan Design Contest.

332
00:21:41,340 --> 00:21:42,840
If I ever get to meet
my father someday,

333
00:21:43,510 --> 00:21:46,640
I want him to acknowledge me
as a designer in my own right.

334
00:22:00,220 --> 00:22:01,930
Well, I...

335
00:22:07,830 --> 00:22:09,770
What is it? Do you recognize that?

336
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:11,300
Well...

337
00:22:11,300 --> 00:22:15,010
This handkerchief. When I was young,
a childhood friend was going abroad,

338
00:22:15,340 --> 00:22:18,140
- so I made it as a farewell gift.
- Oh, my!

339
00:22:23,610 --> 00:22:25,620
Make sure you come back happy.

340
00:22:26,220 --> 00:22:27,220
Okay?

341
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:45,200
You crybaby. It's a farewell gift.

342
00:22:45,700 --> 00:22:46,700
I made it myself.

343
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:49,010
This...

344
00:22:49,940 --> 00:22:51,140
You really made this?

345
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:52,680
Yes.

346
00:22:53,040 --> 00:22:56,680
Whenever you feel like crying,
look at this handkerchief.

347
00:22:58,080 --> 00:23:01,790
Remember me calling you a crybaby,
and your tears will stop.

348
00:23:07,560 --> 00:23:08,560
You know something?

349
00:23:10,460 --> 00:23:14,530
You have a gift
for making people happy.

350
00:23:27,580 --> 00:23:30,780
But to be honest,
I ended up using it more myself.

351
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:34,280
While I was in med school,
which I had no passion for,

352
00:23:34,520 --> 00:23:37,890
I felt lost and kept wondering
if I was on the right path.

353
00:23:38,590 --> 00:23:40,690
Every time I felt that way,
I cried into this handkerchief.

354
00:23:41,660 --> 00:23:44,960
And every time I looked
at this handkerchief,

355
00:23:45,300 --> 00:23:48,770
I'd remember my friend's words
and his bright smile.

356
00:23:50,270 --> 00:23:53,870
"You have a gift
for making people happy."

357
00:23:55,470 --> 00:23:56,940
So I made up my mind.

358
00:23:58,510 --> 00:24:00,480
To become someone
who creates happiness.

359
00:24:06,950 --> 00:24:09,820
But wait, why do you have it?

360
00:24:10,420 --> 00:24:12,260
Did he give it back to you?

361
00:24:12,990 --> 00:24:14,490
My friend doesn't know this, but...

362
00:24:15,190 --> 00:24:18,130
I actually made two
so we could each have one.

363
00:24:19,660 --> 00:24:24,030
Wow, so it was a matching set.
That's so romantic.

364
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:29,470
So was he your first love,
by any chance?

365
00:24:33,780 --> 00:24:36,780
I'd say he means much more to me
than that.

366
00:24:37,150 --> 00:24:41,380
He opened up my world
so I could live as a designer.

367
00:24:55,700 --> 00:24:56,700
Yes.

368
00:24:58,370 --> 00:24:59,470
The Chairman?

369
00:25:02,540 --> 00:25:04,270
Sorry, everyone,
but I have to leave now.

370
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:06,780
Is the Chairman
in critical condition?

371
00:25:06,810 --> 00:25:09,810
I won't know until I get there.
I'll call you when I arrive.

372
00:25:10,450 --> 00:25:11,480
I'm coming with you.

373
00:25:15,290 --> 00:25:18,490
Sorry, everyone.
We'll call you when we get there.

374
00:25:18,720 --> 00:25:20,920
Mr. Park, I'm leaving you in charge.

375
00:25:21,420 --> 00:25:22,430
Got it.

376
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:27,360
All right, then. Let's go.

377
00:25:40,240 --> 00:25:41,880
What timing.

378
00:25:42,780 --> 00:25:44,350
Sorry for ruining the moment.

379
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:48,720
This isn't my only chance.
For today, this is more than enough.

380
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:50,190
See? I told you.

381
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:54,290
I'm telling you, Ju Ah knew
you were Pacu Nacho all along.

382
00:25:55,230 --> 00:25:56,230
I guess so.

383
00:25:56,790 --> 00:26:00,430
My head's spinning,
wondering when she figured it out.

384
00:26:01,930 --> 00:26:04,030
You two have a deeper connection
than I realized.

385
00:26:04,970 --> 00:26:06,370
I was a little envious.

386
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:09,940
Even though you were apart,
your shared memories kept you going.

387
00:26:12,740 --> 00:26:14,410
That's all in the past.

388
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:18,580
The Chairman will be all right,
won't he?

389
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:20,350
He has to be.

390
00:26:21,380 --> 00:26:22,950
It's scary being an only child
at times like this.

391
00:26:24,250 --> 00:26:27,590
If I had any siblings,
I'd have someone to lean on.

392
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:41,440
Why are you so antsy?

393
00:26:42,270 --> 00:26:44,070
Are you that worried
about the Chairman?

394
00:26:44,870 --> 00:26:46,240
Of course, I am.

395
00:26:46,910 --> 00:26:50,650
It's natural to worry when you hear
an elder is sick, isn't it?

396
00:26:51,010 --> 00:26:53,650
You're right. I'm worried, too.

397
00:26:54,950 --> 00:26:57,350
Then why take it out on the fire?

398
00:26:57,550 --> 00:26:59,460
Are you upset
that the Director left?

399
00:26:59,790 --> 00:27:04,430
Upset? Of course, he had to go.
He's an executive, after all.

400
00:27:05,500 --> 00:27:06,760
Look, if you ask me...

401
00:27:06,760 --> 00:27:09,170
I think he and the Vice President
have already talked about you.

402
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:14,470
No matter how you slice it,
this was one heck of a workshop.

403
00:27:15,210 --> 00:27:18,380
One day the Director confesses,
the next day you do.

404
00:27:18,440 --> 00:27:21,780
What confession?
It's all just ancient history.

405
00:27:22,780 --> 00:27:25,880
- Still, things will be different.
- Different? Whatever.

406
00:27:26,780 --> 00:27:29,890
Our families are still enemies,
you know.

407
00:27:34,020 --> 00:27:35,060
It's the Director.

408
00:27:37,260 --> 00:27:38,290
Yes, Director.

409
00:27:39,360 --> 00:27:43,000
Mr. Park, his breathing
was a bit unstable for a moment,

410
00:27:43,100 --> 00:27:45,100
but I waited until he was stable
before I left.

411
00:27:45,940 --> 00:27:50,410
It'd be awkward to go back,
so just carry on without me.

412
00:27:50,940 --> 00:27:53,710
Understood. I'll send you photos.

413
00:27:54,180 --> 00:27:55,680
Yes. See you at the office
in a couple of days.

414
00:27:56,610 --> 00:27:58,480
Wait. Hello?
Gong Ju Ah is right here...

415
00:28:01,990 --> 00:28:02,990
He hung up.

416
00:28:03,990 --> 00:28:06,020
Is the Chairman okay?

417
00:28:06,390 --> 00:28:07,520
Yes, thankfully.

418
00:28:08,290 --> 00:28:10,430
But I wonder
why he didn't ask about you.

419
00:28:11,060 --> 00:28:13,860
Why do you always have to
make things so weird?

420
00:28:14,130 --> 00:28:15,500
Gosh, I'm going to bed.

421
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:32,580
And every time I looked
at this handkerchief,

422
00:28:32,580 --> 00:28:37,120
I'd remember my friend's words
and his bright smile.

423
00:28:37,720 --> 00:28:39,390
So I made up my mind.

424
00:28:41,020 --> 00:28:43,060
To become someone
who creates happiness.

425
00:28:50,230 --> 00:28:53,770
So was he your first love,
by any chance?

426
00:28:54,500 --> 00:28:57,410
I'd say he means much more to me
than that.

427
00:28:58,480 --> 00:29:02,580
He opened up my world
so I could live as a designer.

428
00:29:42,820 --> 00:29:45,920
Wow, this pollack soup is great.
Dae Han.

429
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:49,490
When is your wife getting back?
She'll be back before the move?

430
00:29:52,300 --> 00:29:53,860
She's at her aunt's place.

431
00:29:54,200 --> 00:29:55,930
She said she's going to stay
a few more days.

432
00:29:56,070 --> 00:29:59,940
So that's why you're so down?
Because your wife's away.

433
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,070
Goodness.

434
00:30:02,010 --> 00:30:04,110
- I guess so.
- Woo Jae.

435
00:30:04,970 --> 00:30:07,480
Can you order some supplies
for the pharmacy later?

436
00:30:07,740 --> 00:30:10,080
Sure, but I have an online class
today,

437
00:30:10,150 --> 00:30:11,710
so I'll get it done for you
tomorrow morning.

438
00:30:12,080 --> 00:30:15,150
- Hurry up, you said you were late.
- What?

439
00:30:15,220 --> 00:30:16,220
Yes.

440
00:30:16,550 --> 00:30:17,690
By the way, Dae Han.

441
00:30:17,950 --> 00:30:19,990
That new place you're moving into,
how big is it?

442
00:30:20,390 --> 00:30:21,820
You should be thinking about
when you have kids,

443
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:23,630
so you should've looked
for something bigger...

444
00:30:23,690 --> 00:30:25,800
Gosh, what's gotten into you today?

445
00:30:26,060 --> 00:30:27,460
What? What did I do?

446
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:31,940
Why are you asking about family
you never cared about before?

447
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:35,640
Unbelievable. One minute you're mad
I don't care about family matters,

448
00:30:35,910 --> 00:30:39,010
and the next you're mad that I do.
I can't win with you, seriously.

449
00:30:39,140 --> 00:30:41,440
Gong Dae Han, finish up.
We need to go.

450
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:44,510
- Let's go. Time for our workout.
- Yes.

451
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:46,280
Unbelievable.

452
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:51,450
So what are we going to do?

453
00:30:52,060 --> 00:30:54,790
What can we do? We should just wait.

454
00:30:56,030 --> 00:30:58,290
He'll be back when his money's gone,
won't he?

455
00:30:58,430 --> 00:31:00,830
Are you crazy?
You'd really take him back?

456
00:31:04,770 --> 00:31:06,000
Hello, sir.

457
00:31:06,640 --> 00:31:08,440
Have you heard from Ji Hu's Dad?

458
00:31:08,570 --> 00:31:11,270
Heard from him?
I should be asking you that.

459
00:31:11,370 --> 00:31:13,580
He has until the end of the day
to return the items or pay for them.

460
00:31:13,640 --> 00:31:14,680
If he doesn't pay up,

461
00:31:14,740 --> 00:31:16,980
I'm reporting him
to the police for theft.

462
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:20,180
Wait, how much is it in total?

463
00:31:22,050 --> 00:31:23,320
Thirty thousand dollars?

464
00:31:24,050 --> 00:31:26,420
How are we supposed to come up
with that kind of money right now?

465
00:31:26,720 --> 00:31:28,290
Gosh, I can't deal with this!

466
00:31:30,190 --> 00:31:31,530
This is driving me crazy!

467
00:31:31,590 --> 00:31:35,060
What's to go crazy about?
Let him get reported and caught.

468
00:31:35,870 --> 00:31:39,200
I'll give you back
the money you gave me,

469
00:31:39,270 --> 00:31:41,340
so you can pay for the items first.

470
00:31:41,840 --> 00:31:45,140
But what about the money
for your designer rentals?

471
00:31:45,410 --> 00:31:48,680
That... I'll figure something out.

472
00:31:48,950 --> 00:31:50,850
And how are you going to do that?

473
00:31:51,550 --> 00:31:54,680
Exactly. How will you manage
without my father's permission...

474
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:56,020
to spend money?

475
00:31:56,150 --> 00:31:59,020
Well, I'm sure there's a way.

476
00:31:59,860 --> 00:32:03,460
What a waste of that Cabanel bag.
I never even got to use it.

477
00:32:03,730 --> 00:32:06,460
Auntie, why on earth
did you marry a guy like that?

478
00:32:07,060 --> 00:32:09,570
When your dad was pushing me
to get married,

479
00:32:09,800 --> 00:32:12,370
he was the only man
who was interested in me.

480
00:32:13,270 --> 00:32:17,870
- Divorce him. Find a good man.
- Hey.

481
00:32:18,170 --> 00:32:19,680
What decent man would be...

482
00:32:20,810 --> 00:32:22,550
crazy enough to date me?

483
00:32:30,150 --> 00:32:32,660
(Pharmacy)

484
00:32:36,330 --> 00:32:37,690
Mom, it's about Hui Gyeong.

485
00:32:39,060 --> 00:32:41,000
She got her certification
a few months ago.

486
00:32:42,700 --> 00:32:45,270
So she got it and still went out,
saying she was studying?

487
00:32:46,100 --> 00:32:47,100
Yes.

488
00:32:48,240 --> 00:32:50,310
It looked like she was checking out
properties in Ganghwa,

489
00:32:51,110 --> 00:32:52,140
so I went to check it out.

490
00:32:52,580 --> 00:32:55,410
But Ganghwa is so close.

491
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:58,650
Unbelievable. She's got some nerve.

492
00:33:02,790 --> 00:33:03,950
And the fact that
she's seeing another man...

493
00:33:04,590 --> 00:33:05,920
How did you find out?

494
00:33:06,860 --> 00:33:10,190
I just... I happened to overhear it.

495
00:33:12,060 --> 00:33:13,330
So, what now?

496
00:33:14,830 --> 00:33:15,830
Mom.

497
00:33:16,970 --> 00:33:18,000
What about you?

498
00:33:19,370 --> 00:33:20,970
Why didn't you ever look for Dad?

499
00:33:25,040 --> 00:33:27,680
I figured, what good would it do
to see that mess with my own eyes?

500
00:33:30,550 --> 00:33:31,550
But...

501
00:33:32,220 --> 00:33:33,550
now I regret it.

502
00:33:35,320 --> 00:33:38,350
If only
I had gotten closure back then.

503
00:33:39,790 --> 00:33:42,290
If I'd seen it for myself
and just cut him out of my heart.

504
00:33:44,730 --> 00:33:45,830
For all those years,

505
00:33:46,760 --> 00:33:49,600
I wouldn't have spent all that time
waiting and hoping he'd come back.

506
00:33:53,670 --> 00:33:55,300
You need to get a divorce.

507
00:33:56,110 --> 00:33:57,810
You can't go on living like this.

508
00:33:59,010 --> 00:34:00,010
Okay.

509
00:34:03,550 --> 00:34:04,950
It's a number I don't recognize.

510
00:34:07,150 --> 00:34:08,250
Hello? Who is this?

511
00:34:11,720 --> 00:34:13,220
It's a friend. Just a friend.

512
00:34:14,320 --> 00:34:15,320
Bring you what?

513
00:34:23,970 --> 00:34:24,970
How much is it?

514
00:34:27,200 --> 00:34:28,540
Hey, forget it.

515
00:34:29,470 --> 00:34:30,670
Is this why you called?

516
00:34:31,210 --> 00:34:32,210
Because the other pharmacies
are too far?

517
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:33,480
No, that's not it.

518
00:34:34,540 --> 00:34:35,850
I went to the clinic to see you,

519
00:34:35,850 --> 00:34:37,180
but they said
you were at the pharmacy.

520
00:34:38,310 --> 00:34:39,320
So I got your number.

521
00:34:40,280 --> 00:34:41,320
So why were you looking for me?

522
00:34:42,890 --> 00:34:44,250
To tell me not to spread
rumors about you?

523
00:34:45,220 --> 00:34:48,660
That's right.
I won't talk if you don't.

524
00:34:50,160 --> 00:34:51,230
Okay, fine. Deal.

525
00:34:55,800 --> 00:34:58,730
Everyone at the market knows
why I'm living with my family.

526
00:34:59,400 --> 00:35:01,540
If they find out
that jerk is in money trouble again,

527
00:35:03,210 --> 00:35:04,970
I'll be too humiliated
to even show my face.

528
00:35:10,150 --> 00:35:11,350
How much did he run off with?

529
00:35:13,550 --> 00:35:15,050
All the money we've saved up,

530
00:35:15,690 --> 00:35:17,320
plus the stolen designer goods...

531
00:35:18,490 --> 00:35:19,920
It must be at least 100,000 dollars.

532
00:35:20,220 --> 00:35:21,220
A hundred thousand dollars?

533
00:35:22,330 --> 00:35:24,690
I have to go. Thanks for the drink.

534
00:35:26,360 --> 00:35:27,360
Hey.

535
00:35:36,210 --> 00:35:37,210
Gosh, you startled me.

536
00:35:41,010 --> 00:35:42,010
Did you hear all that?

537
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:47,250
Please pretend
you didn't hear anything.

538
00:35:49,050 --> 00:35:50,050
I didn't hear a thing.

539
00:36:02,730 --> 00:36:05,740
(Warm and Reliable Police)

540
00:36:05,800 --> 00:36:07,170
Thank you so much
for your help yesterday.

541
00:36:07,940 --> 00:36:10,870
I'll be sure to repay this favor.

542
00:36:11,010 --> 00:36:13,240
Please. It was nothing.

543
00:36:13,540 --> 00:36:15,580
No, really. You were a huge help.

544
00:36:17,710 --> 00:36:20,920
Chief, sorry about the other day.
I apologize.

545
00:36:20,980 --> 00:36:22,220
Don't worry about it.

546
00:36:23,550 --> 00:36:24,550
Well, then.

547
00:36:24,890 --> 00:36:25,890
Mr. Gong.

548
00:36:26,620 --> 00:36:27,720
I...

549
00:36:28,590 --> 00:36:31,790
- I have the license plate number.
- Sorry?

550
00:36:31,930 --> 00:36:35,730
Yes, I saw it on the store's CCTV
and jotted down the number.

551
00:36:36,230 --> 00:36:38,130
- Really?
- But...

552
00:36:38,400 --> 00:36:41,040
we can't give you the number
or run a check on it.

553
00:36:41,700 --> 00:36:44,470
If you file an official report,
then we can help.

554
00:36:44,540 --> 00:36:46,540
- Can't you just tell me the number?
- We can't.

555
00:36:51,380 --> 00:36:52,480
(We're here to help with anything.)

556
00:36:52,680 --> 00:36:53,720
Right.

557
00:36:54,420 --> 00:36:55,420
No, that's okay.

558
00:36:57,220 --> 00:36:58,220
Never mind.

559
00:37:02,960 --> 00:37:03,960
Oh, wait...

560
00:37:06,230 --> 00:37:09,130
Oh, man. You were right, Chief.

561
00:37:09,970 --> 00:37:10,970
See?

562
00:37:11,470 --> 00:37:13,700
Sometimes, ignorance is bliss.

563
00:37:14,940 --> 00:37:17,610
He might change his mind,

564
00:37:17,970 --> 00:37:20,280
- so I'll hang on to it.
- Good idea.

565
00:37:24,950 --> 00:37:27,150
(License Plate: 314 J9542)

566
00:37:27,320 --> 00:37:29,550
(Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association)

567
00:37:31,550 --> 00:37:32,560
Darn it.

568
00:37:34,990 --> 00:37:37,730
Hey, what do you think you're doing?

569
00:37:38,330 --> 00:37:41,600
Hey, for plastic bottles,
peel the label and crush them flat.

570
00:37:41,860 --> 00:37:43,370
And sort the glass bottles by color.

571
00:37:43,370 --> 00:37:45,330
Brown, green, and clear.
Separate them.

572
00:37:45,670 --> 00:37:48,640
- Seriously.
- What do you want from me?

573
00:37:49,710 --> 00:37:53,980
- Have you ever recycled before?
- Yes... What?

574
00:37:56,610 --> 00:37:58,380
Keep that up,
and you'll get divorced again.

575
00:37:58,380 --> 00:37:59,880
Hey, no need to make it personal.

576
00:37:59,980 --> 00:38:03,650
You need to learn to do this right.
And do some housework for a change.

577
00:38:03,990 --> 00:38:08,520
Sort white and colored Styrofoam.
Clean plastic bags get recycled,

578
00:38:08,620 --> 00:38:09,990
and dirty plastic goes
in the regular trash.

579
00:38:10,330 --> 00:38:11,760
Gosh, honestly.

580
00:38:12,230 --> 00:38:13,560
This is some disgusting trash,

581
00:38:14,200 --> 00:38:15,200
and there's so much of it.

582
00:38:19,270 --> 00:38:22,370
Gosh, this guy doesn't get
that these bags cost money!

583
00:38:22,570 --> 00:38:25,880
Stomp it down to pack it tight!
Seriously...

584
00:38:25,940 --> 00:38:27,080
Hey, I already stuffed it full!

585
00:38:27,140 --> 00:38:30,080
You can fit more if you stomp on it!
Hurry, stomp it down! Stomp!

586
00:38:30,580 --> 00:38:33,820
Hurry! Come on!
Are you even thinking? Seriously.

587
00:38:33,880 --> 00:38:35,620
- Just a second.
- For crying out loud.

588
00:38:36,720 --> 00:38:40,690
Would you stop fooling around?
Just stomp on it! Hurry!

589
00:38:40,890 --> 00:38:44,990
- Just like this?
- Yes, it's open. Now stomp it down!

590
00:38:45,060 --> 00:38:47,800
- Pack it tight. Yes.
- Do we really have to do this?

591
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:50,030
Harder! Push down harder! Go on.

592
00:38:50,100 --> 00:38:52,700
Come on!
You have to stomp on it harder!

593
00:38:52,770 --> 00:38:54,900
- You're a big guy, use your weight!
- Goodness.

594
00:38:54,900 --> 00:38:55,970
Tighter! That's it!

595
00:38:56,710 --> 00:38:59,480
There you go! Good job, Dr. Yang.

596
00:38:59,580 --> 00:39:02,610
- Great job! Way to go!
- Gosh!

597
00:39:03,350 --> 00:39:04,350
Hold on.

598
00:39:05,820 --> 00:39:06,850
What?

599
00:39:11,250 --> 00:39:14,560
Food waste must be separated! Hey!
Over here! The food waste goes here!

600
00:39:16,060 --> 00:39:17,060
Darn it...

601
00:39:17,860 --> 00:39:19,630
Gosh, so embarrassing. Seriously.

602
00:39:20,360 --> 00:39:21,560
And of all things,
I was wearing white pants.

603
00:39:22,060 --> 00:39:23,070
Will this stain come out?

604
00:39:36,310 --> 00:39:37,380
Oh, my, Doctor!

605
00:39:40,380 --> 00:39:41,420
At this hour,

606
00:39:42,020 --> 00:39:43,050
what brings you here?

607
00:39:44,190 --> 00:39:45,920
I took some time off.

608
00:39:47,460 --> 00:39:52,030
Don't say you lost all your patients
because of that rumor I started.

609
00:39:54,000 --> 00:39:55,130
Back then...

610
00:39:55,730 --> 00:39:59,540
I was so terribly sorry.
Gosh, I must've been out of my mind.

611
00:40:00,270 --> 00:40:01,840
Anyway, congratulations.

612
00:40:02,100 --> 00:40:04,210
On Dr. Yang becoming Vice President
of the Merchants' Association.

613
00:40:04,810 --> 00:40:05,810
Thank you.

614
00:40:06,810 --> 00:40:09,210
I appreciate that, but...

615
00:40:09,380 --> 00:40:11,910
Dr. Gong is just so mean.

616
00:40:12,250 --> 00:40:15,950
He torments and bullies my husband
like a bratty little kid.

617
00:40:17,050 --> 00:40:18,050
He says it's hard?

618
00:40:18,790 --> 00:40:21,860
And to think he got on his knees
and begged for any work at all.

619
00:40:22,320 --> 00:40:23,330
Oh, my.

620
00:40:24,360 --> 00:40:27,030
Dr. Gong must've been bluffing
in front of you, Doctor.

621
00:40:27,200 --> 00:40:29,400
My husband did not get on his knees.

622
00:40:29,470 --> 00:40:33,540
Oh, come on. Dong Ik must have been
embarrassed, so he lied to his wife.

623
00:40:34,470 --> 00:40:35,600
He got down on his knees.

624
00:40:38,010 --> 00:40:39,310
That's impossible.

625
00:40:40,340 --> 00:40:42,140
Do you have proof?

626
00:40:42,750 --> 00:40:43,850
I do.

627
00:40:44,650 --> 00:40:46,580
I learned from someone recently.

628
00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:48,750
The importance of having proof.

629
00:40:51,590 --> 00:40:52,590
Well, then...

630
00:41:03,430 --> 00:41:06,300
Gong Jeong Han, that jerk.
I knew it.

631
00:41:06,600 --> 00:41:09,810
I knew he'd go running to Seong Mi.
That jerk!

632
00:41:10,440 --> 00:41:11,440
Honey.

633
00:41:11,810 --> 00:41:14,810
- Is that what's important now?
- It's humiliating!

634
00:41:14,980 --> 00:41:16,810
You think that's the problem here?

635
00:41:17,410 --> 00:41:18,610
Then what is?

636
00:41:18,980 --> 00:41:20,780
If that video ever gets out,

637
00:41:21,180 --> 00:41:24,050
it'll definitely be an obstacle
when you run for city council.

638
00:41:24,450 --> 00:41:27,220
Then what do we do?

639
00:41:28,020 --> 00:41:29,990
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

640
00:41:37,900 --> 00:41:41,270
You must get your hands
on Dr. Gong's phone.

641
00:41:41,700 --> 00:41:44,370
What good will that do?
I don't know the password.

642
00:41:45,270 --> 00:41:47,310
It's definitely a backwards L.

643
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:49,780
Or maybe just an L.

644
00:41:52,980 --> 00:41:56,120
Whatever it takes,
find out the password first.

645
00:42:17,410 --> 00:42:18,570
What the...

646
00:42:19,010 --> 00:42:20,210
Why show your face
to the phone like that?

647
00:42:20,510 --> 00:42:24,250
Oh, this? It's facial recognition.
It's easy to use with one hand. Why?

648
00:42:24,680 --> 00:42:27,380
Oh, I see. I was just curious.

649
00:42:27,820 --> 00:42:30,350
What's this? Did you text me?

650
00:42:30,920 --> 00:42:31,920
- What?
- Oh, I...

651
00:42:32,560 --> 00:42:34,190
"You're working so hard?"

652
00:42:34,620 --> 00:42:36,730
That's just how I feel.

653
00:42:37,290 --> 00:42:39,460
You're ridiculous. Seriously.

654
00:42:44,470 --> 00:42:48,000
Once you figure out the password,
think of Muhammad Ali.

655
00:42:49,840 --> 00:42:54,110
- Who?
- Muhammad...

656
00:42:54,580 --> 00:42:55,640
Ali.

657
00:42:58,410 --> 00:42:59,580
Float like a butterfly,

658
00:43:00,250 --> 00:43:01,580
sting like a bee.

659
00:43:08,590 --> 00:43:09,590
Hey, Jeong Han.

660
00:43:10,130 --> 00:43:11,130
What?

661
00:43:12,330 --> 00:43:13,330
Jeong Han.

662
00:43:13,930 --> 00:43:14,960
Gosh, what is it?

663
00:43:16,130 --> 00:43:18,570
- What the... What are you doing?
- Unlocking it.

664
00:43:19,230 --> 00:43:22,570
- What?
- There. Mission complete.

665
00:43:23,410 --> 00:43:26,010
Hey, you! You little punk!
Hey! You...

666
00:43:30,950 --> 00:43:33,150
Hey, Bucket! You little punk!

667
00:43:34,220 --> 00:43:35,320
You little jerk!

668
00:43:36,420 --> 00:43:40,820
Hey, you! Get back here!
Are you crazy? You little jerk!

669
00:43:41,390 --> 00:43:43,930
Hey, you jerk! You punk!

670
00:43:49,400 --> 00:43:52,200
- Hey! Bucket!
- Stop chasing me, darn it.

671
00:43:52,270 --> 00:43:54,470
Stop right there! Hey!

672
00:43:54,540 --> 00:43:58,310
(Grandma's Home-Style Gukbap)

673
00:43:58,370 --> 00:44:01,180
Bucket! You're dead if I catch you!

674
00:44:07,420 --> 00:44:08,780
Come on, where is it?
Why won't this work?

675
00:44:09,280 --> 00:44:11,350
Gosh, where is it? Come on, please.

676
00:44:13,520 --> 00:44:16,330
- This isn't it. That's not me.
- Bucket.

677
00:44:19,660 --> 00:44:20,660
Oh, man.

678
00:44:22,030 --> 00:44:23,030
Looking for the video?

679
00:44:23,700 --> 00:44:25,670
You think you'd find it there?

680
00:44:26,840 --> 00:44:29,040
- Then where is it?
- Do your homework.

681
00:44:29,370 --> 00:44:34,240
- It's saved forever on the cloud.
- Darn... So why did you chase me?

682
00:44:35,680 --> 00:44:40,220
Because it was fun. Come on.
Man, you're fast when you run away.

683
00:44:40,550 --> 00:44:41,880
- Darn you...
- See you in the morning.

684
00:44:42,450 --> 00:44:44,490
You slippery eel.

685
00:44:45,090 --> 00:44:46,120
You rotten jerk!

686
00:44:47,920 --> 00:44:50,330
Ouch, it hurts.

687
00:44:50,430 --> 00:44:53,130
Somebody help me.

688
00:44:54,430 --> 00:44:56,330
Man, It really hurts.

689
00:45:00,740 --> 00:45:02,970
My gosh, honey.

690
00:45:04,810 --> 00:45:07,410
- What's with this mess?
- Oh, no. What happened?

691
00:45:07,740 --> 00:45:09,340
Oh, my goodness.
Look at all this sweat.

692
00:45:09,710 --> 00:45:11,350
Dad, your foot is bleeding.

693
00:45:12,980 --> 00:45:16,250
Gosh, Father.
I'll go get a bandage from the room.

694
00:45:16,650 --> 00:45:19,250
- Oh, no.
- What were you doing out there?

695
00:45:20,220 --> 00:45:23,230
Does he work for the association
with his fists? Right, Grandpa?

696
00:45:23,290 --> 00:45:25,860
His medical bills will cost more
than he earns.

697
00:45:25,860 --> 00:45:26,860
Quiet!

698
00:45:27,760 --> 00:45:30,530
A freeloader like you has no right
to worry about his medical bills.

699
00:45:30,830 --> 00:45:33,470
I was just saying...
Gosh, unbelievable.

700
00:45:33,540 --> 00:45:36,110
There's no one on my side
in this house. Is there?

701
00:45:41,710 --> 00:45:42,710
The clinic.

702
00:45:44,150 --> 00:45:45,150
The clinic.

703
00:45:48,050 --> 00:45:49,450
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic,
Yang Seon Chul)

704
00:45:49,520 --> 00:45:50,520
(Date Dispensed: February 14, 2026)

705
00:45:53,420 --> 00:45:54,490
Why is this...

706
00:45:56,530 --> 00:45:57,530
My gosh.

707
00:45:58,530 --> 00:45:59,530
Father.

708
00:45:59,900 --> 00:46:04,770
- Did you get treatment from here?
- What?

709
00:46:05,830 --> 00:46:06,840
Yes.

710
00:46:07,040 --> 00:46:11,010
Dad, don't we have an unspoken rule
that we don't go to that clinic?

711
00:46:11,070 --> 00:46:12,170
Quiet! Give that here.

712
00:46:12,410 --> 00:46:15,380
But what's wrong, Father?
Where are you feeling sick?

713
00:46:15,640 --> 00:46:17,880
You should have told me.

714
00:46:17,950 --> 00:46:19,880
It's nothing serious.
Just give it here.

715
00:46:19,950 --> 00:46:20,950
Wait, hold on a second, Father.

716
00:46:22,550 --> 00:46:24,350
But the fill date...

717
00:46:25,050 --> 00:46:27,620
is the day before
the Association President Election.

718
00:46:28,520 --> 00:46:30,360
So what about it?

719
00:46:31,190 --> 00:46:32,190
Dad, don't tell me...

720
00:46:33,300 --> 00:46:36,230
Dad, don't tell me
you voted for Jeong Han.

721
00:46:38,170 --> 00:46:39,970
- You didn't, right?
- I said, quiet!

722
00:46:42,040 --> 00:46:44,040
Dad, why didn't you answer me
back then?

723
00:46:45,040 --> 00:46:46,040
Answer what?

724
00:46:46,680 --> 00:46:47,680
Father.

725
00:46:47,980 --> 00:46:50,110
In exchange for the treatment,

726
00:46:50,680 --> 00:46:51,880
did they ask you for your vote?

727
00:46:52,110 --> 00:46:55,720
No. Jeong Han's not
that kind of person.

728
00:46:55,850 --> 00:46:58,220
He was just doing
his duty as a doctor.

729
00:46:58,550 --> 00:46:59,620
So you did vote for him.

730
00:47:00,420 --> 00:47:02,520
You voted for that jerk
and not for me.

731
00:47:04,260 --> 00:47:05,260
Father.

732
00:47:05,830 --> 00:47:07,500
Please tell us the truth.

733
00:47:08,560 --> 00:47:10,200
Fine, I voted for him.

734
00:47:11,170 --> 00:47:12,200
I voted for Gong Jeong Han.

735
00:47:13,240 --> 00:47:15,540
So what? It's my choice.

736
00:47:15,940 --> 00:47:16,940
Father!

737
00:47:18,010 --> 00:47:19,010
Get out!

738
00:47:30,550 --> 00:47:31,620
So was he...

739
00:47:32,350 --> 00:47:33,890
your first love, by any chance?

740
00:47:36,490 --> 00:47:39,130
I'd say he means much more to me
than that.

741
00:47:39,830 --> 00:47:43,770
He opened up my world
so I could live as a designer.

742
00:47:45,800 --> 00:47:47,870
Why did I say that?

743
00:47:49,340 --> 00:47:52,210
I'm cringing so hard right now.
Seriously.

744
00:47:54,680 --> 00:47:55,810
What was it like seeing her again?

745
00:47:56,210 --> 00:47:57,210
Do you still have feelings for her?

746
00:47:58,110 --> 00:47:59,110
I do.

747
00:48:07,090 --> 00:48:09,860
He still likes me? Good grief.

748
00:48:11,830 --> 00:48:16,300
But now, what do I do?
Should I pretend I don't know?

749
00:48:17,270 --> 00:48:20,470
I acted like I recognized him,
but he just pretended not to.

750
00:48:20,940 --> 00:48:22,070
So should I still pretend
I don't know?

751
00:48:26,640 --> 00:48:27,640
What is going on?

752
00:48:31,610 --> 00:48:32,610
Yes, Director.

753
00:48:33,180 --> 00:48:34,180
Gong Ju Ah.

754
00:48:36,520 --> 00:48:37,520
Gong Ju Ah?

755
00:48:38,290 --> 00:48:39,290
That's right. Ju Ah.

756
00:48:40,420 --> 00:48:41,420
It's me.

757
00:48:42,560 --> 00:48:43,560
Yang Hyun Bin.

758
00:48:47,200 --> 00:48:48,460
I'm back.

759
00:48:50,100 --> 00:48:52,600
Yes. Hyun Bin.

760
00:48:53,700 --> 00:48:54,900
If you have a minute,

761
00:48:55,870 --> 00:48:56,940
could you come out?

762
00:48:58,510 --> 00:49:00,780
Right now? Where are you?

763
00:49:02,410 --> 00:49:05,480
The last place we saw each other.

764
00:50:49,050 --> 00:50:51,250
So you're really back,
Yang Hyun Bin.

765
00:50:52,350 --> 00:50:53,360
Yes.

766
00:50:54,220 --> 00:50:55,220
Have you been well?

767
00:50:55,820 --> 00:50:56,830
Yes.

768
00:50:59,260 --> 00:51:00,260
What about you?

769
00:51:01,100 --> 00:51:02,130
Did you find your happiness?

770
00:51:06,170 --> 00:51:07,540
I made up my mind right then.

771
00:51:07,970 --> 00:51:11,270
I had to be happy, no matter what,
and I would never cry again.

772
00:51:11,410 --> 00:51:14,010
So that if I ever met her again
someday...

773
00:51:15,480 --> 00:51:17,880
I wanted her to be proud
of the life I'd lived.

774
00:51:19,350 --> 00:51:20,580
You did well.

775
00:51:21,620 --> 00:51:24,090
You've lived a very good life,
Yang Hyun Bin.

776
00:51:26,050 --> 00:51:27,060
Thanks to you.

777
00:51:28,260 --> 00:51:30,390
It's good to see you again,
Yang Hyun Bin.

778
00:51:37,770 --> 00:51:38,770
I've missed you,

779
00:51:39,700 --> 00:51:40,700
Gong Ju Ah.

780
00:51:57,490 --> 00:52:00,520
I wish we could have met like this
from the very beginning.

781
00:52:01,290 --> 00:52:02,290
Tell me about it.

782
00:52:03,020 --> 00:52:05,890
We took the long way around
to get here.

783
00:52:08,660 --> 00:52:11,930
I'm sorry I had to leave yesterday
without a chance to talk.

784
00:52:12,370 --> 00:52:13,900
We were at a workshop,

785
00:52:13,900 --> 00:52:17,140
so it felt wrong
to talk in front of the staff.

786
00:52:17,840 --> 00:52:18,910
Of course, I understand.

787
00:52:19,880 --> 00:52:21,910
So when did you figure out
it was me?

788
00:52:22,280 --> 00:52:23,750
At that chicken soup restaurant?

789
00:52:24,550 --> 00:52:28,780
No, Gaetdari Samhap.
When you were drunk and sang for me.

790
00:52:31,350 --> 00:52:34,820
- Why didn't you say anything then?
- You're the one who ran off.

791
00:52:35,590 --> 00:52:38,790
- I did?
- And you treated me like a creep.

792
00:52:40,960 --> 00:52:41,960
Sorry.

793
00:52:45,100 --> 00:52:48,270
Waiting for you to recognize me
was torture.

794
00:52:48,640 --> 00:52:51,940
How was I supposed to recognize you?
You've changed so much.

795
00:52:52,540 --> 00:52:53,540
That's a relief.

796
00:52:53,840 --> 00:52:56,410
I worked really hard to change,
you know.

797
00:52:57,650 --> 00:53:00,220
But then why didn't you say anything
after you knew it was me?

798
00:53:01,450 --> 00:53:04,450
I mean, come on.
You're the director.

799
00:53:06,660 --> 00:53:08,790
Let's just be casual
outside of work.

800
00:53:09,520 --> 00:53:10,530
Okay.

801
00:53:11,130 --> 00:53:14,000
Then you have to treat me
like your big sister.

802
00:53:14,230 --> 00:53:15,830
What? No, thanks.

803
00:53:17,930 --> 00:53:19,000
My gosh.

804
00:53:20,770 --> 00:53:21,770
Ju Ah?

805
00:53:23,540 --> 00:53:25,510
- Hey, brother.
- What?

806
00:53:26,810 --> 00:53:28,780
- Is that your brother?
- Yes.

807
00:53:28,840 --> 00:53:31,910
Woo Jae... You remember the director
from my company, right?

808
00:53:32,050 --> 00:53:33,050
Yang Hyun Bin.

809
00:53:33,420 --> 00:53:34,420
Hello.

810
00:53:35,080 --> 00:53:36,590
Hey, Woo Jae. Long time no see.

811
00:53:37,350 --> 00:53:39,350
I almost
wouldn't have recognized you.

812
00:53:40,260 --> 00:53:42,290
By the way, Eun Bin,
what are you doing here?

813
00:53:43,630 --> 00:53:47,300
We have a date tomorrow, so
I gave Woo Jae the matching shirts.

814
00:53:47,360 --> 00:53:50,670
Then he offered to walk me home,
so we were on our way...

815
00:53:51,300 --> 00:53:55,800
- And then we saw you.
- Wait, hang on. What? A date?

816
00:53:56,040 --> 00:53:57,040
Matching shirts?

817
00:53:57,670 --> 00:53:59,810
Hey, let's talk at home.

818
00:54:00,910 --> 00:54:02,410
Right, let's go home, Eun Bin.

819
00:54:02,710 --> 00:54:04,880
Hey, you'll be in huge trouble
if anyone sees you together.

820
00:54:04,950 --> 00:54:07,220
Right? If my stepmom saw
the four of us together,

821
00:54:07,280 --> 00:54:08,680
she'd totally flip out,
wouldn't she?

822
00:54:09,350 --> 00:54:12,850
I'm so happy.
I think my wish is coming true.

823
00:54:13,560 --> 00:54:16,290
- What wish?
- Double in-laws.

824
00:54:20,130 --> 00:54:21,960
Hey, let's go.

825
00:54:22,660 --> 00:54:26,170
- Ms. Gong, I'll see you at work.
- Yes, Director. Get home safe.

826
00:54:26,970 --> 00:54:28,970
Woo Jae, see you tomorrow.
And I'll see you again!

827
00:54:29,400 --> 00:54:30,840
Or should I say sister-in-law?

828
00:54:31,510 --> 00:54:33,880
Hey, let's go. Come on. Bye.

829
00:54:33,940 --> 00:54:37,010
We're going the same way,
so let's go. See you, sister-in-law!

830
00:54:37,350 --> 00:54:38,350
Why, you...

831
00:54:42,180 --> 00:54:44,290
I'm telling you,
we're not really dating.

832
00:54:44,520 --> 00:54:46,920
Explain the date
and the matching shirts.

833
00:54:46,920 --> 00:54:49,020
Spit it out. Five, four, three...

834
00:54:49,090 --> 00:54:51,190
Eun Bin told me it was her stepmom
who spread the rumor...

835
00:54:51,190 --> 00:54:52,960
that our mom was having an affair.

836
00:54:53,660 --> 00:54:54,730
So?

837
00:54:54,800 --> 00:54:58,800
She said I owe her. Because of her,
our dad won the election.

838
00:54:58,870 --> 00:55:00,540
So I just agreed
to go out with her once.

839
00:55:00,840 --> 00:55:03,340
- Are you sure?
- Yes, I'm sure.

840
00:55:04,010 --> 00:55:08,540
You're one to talk. What about you?
You said you'd ignore him,

841
00:55:08,780 --> 00:55:11,750
so why were you so cozy at the cafe?
What if our parents find out?

842
00:55:11,980 --> 00:55:14,150
Who do you think
you're talking back to?

843
00:55:14,350 --> 00:55:15,350
Eyes down!

844
00:55:15,420 --> 00:55:17,690
I am looking down!
You're just shorter than me.

845
00:55:17,750 --> 00:55:19,450
Quiet!
Enough with the constant back talk.

846
00:55:21,060 --> 00:55:23,560
So, nothing happened at home, right?

847
00:55:24,890 --> 00:55:26,430
Yes, nothing.

848
00:55:26,800 --> 00:55:28,660
What was that? You hesitated.

849
00:55:29,530 --> 00:55:30,930
Something happened, didn't it?

850
00:55:33,500 --> 00:55:36,910
Eyes front. What is it? Spill it.

851
00:55:39,010 --> 00:55:42,540
- Hey. Headlock for old time's sake?
- No.

852
00:55:47,050 --> 00:55:49,820
It's about Uncle.

853
00:55:50,320 --> 00:55:51,390
What about Uncle?

854
00:55:59,590 --> 00:56:00,630
Uncle.

855
00:56:02,060 --> 00:56:03,060
Ju Ah.

856
00:56:04,370 --> 00:56:06,870
- How was your workshop?
- It was fine.

857
00:56:07,340 --> 00:56:08,840
What are you watching, Uncle?

858
00:56:09,640 --> 00:56:10,870
Just flipping through channels.

859
00:56:12,070 --> 00:56:14,310
- Can I have a beer?
- Of course.

860
00:56:16,440 --> 00:56:19,080
This is nice. Here, cheers.

861
00:56:20,150 --> 00:56:21,150
Cheers.

862
00:56:24,350 --> 00:56:25,820
Goodness.

863
00:56:32,460 --> 00:56:34,030
Uncle...

864
00:56:56,250 --> 00:56:58,120
Gong Jeong Han, that jerk.

865
00:57:00,120 --> 00:57:01,460
Are you that upset, honey?

866
00:57:02,260 --> 00:57:04,030
Ever since we were kids,
they always compared us.

867
00:57:04,790 --> 00:57:06,690
It was always, "Jeong Han this,
Jeong Han that."

868
00:57:07,630 --> 00:57:10,230
But still.
How could he not vote for me?

869
00:57:12,000 --> 00:57:13,070
Honey.

870
00:57:18,210 --> 00:57:19,370
This is really depressing.

871
00:57:36,120 --> 00:57:38,730
Grandpa, you really went too far
this time.

872
00:57:39,390 --> 00:57:42,200
Exactly, Dad.
After seeing how hard he worked,

873
00:57:42,400 --> 00:57:43,630
how could you vote
for the other guy?

874
00:57:45,100 --> 00:57:49,700
Dad's so petty, he'll sulk forever.
He's even skipping breakfast.

875
00:57:53,210 --> 00:57:54,910
You all can go ahead and eat.

876
00:57:55,410 --> 00:57:56,950
I don't really have
an appetite either.

877
00:57:58,280 --> 00:57:59,950
It was all for Dong Ik's sake.

878
00:58:01,820 --> 00:58:04,850
Jeong Han has no political ambition,

879
00:58:05,190 --> 00:58:07,190
so he would do a proper job.

880
00:58:07,790 --> 00:58:08,790
Dong Ik, on the other hand...

881
00:58:09,690 --> 00:58:13,290
His only goal was getting elected,
so he would've ignored his duties.

882
00:58:13,960 --> 00:58:15,930
I guess you're right.

883
00:58:16,400 --> 00:58:19,530
If that happened, he would've
lost his run for council.

884
00:58:20,270 --> 00:58:24,140
He must win people over for votes,
just like he's doing now.

885
00:58:25,170 --> 00:58:29,180
You're absolutely right, Father.
Then please, enjoy the food.

886
00:58:30,750 --> 00:58:31,810
How much do you want?

887
00:58:35,120 --> 00:58:37,790
I'll give it to you as an apology.

888
00:58:38,820 --> 00:58:40,820
How much will it take
to make things right?

889
00:58:43,830 --> 00:58:45,630
Forty thousand dollars, Father.

890
00:58:49,360 --> 00:58:50,370
Done.

891
00:58:57,210 --> 00:58:58,270
Forty thousand?

892
00:59:06,450 --> 00:59:09,320
Dad always takes your side.

893
00:59:09,320 --> 00:59:11,050
Forty thousand dollars,
just like that.

894
00:59:11,450 --> 00:59:13,820
Isn't this what they call
a blessing in disguise?

895
00:59:14,120 --> 00:59:15,960
Such is life.

896
00:59:17,190 --> 00:59:21,560
I'm going to get ready.
Could you do the dishes first?

897
00:59:21,630 --> 00:59:24,230
Of course.
You think I'd only do the dishes?

898
00:59:24,430 --> 00:59:27,300
I'll do anything.
Where are you off to?

899
00:59:27,770 --> 00:59:31,340
A lady I met in a class
at the community center told me...

900
00:59:31,570 --> 00:59:35,510
about a private detective agency
great for finding runaway husbands.

901
00:59:35,940 --> 00:59:37,150
A private detective agency?

902
00:59:38,780 --> 00:59:43,320
- A lawyer?
- Yes. I know a family lawyer.

903
00:59:43,750 --> 00:59:46,250
I'm going to go talk to them
about our realistic options.

904
00:59:46,960 --> 00:59:48,490
Okay.

905
00:59:50,060 --> 00:59:51,330
I thought you were heading out
today.

906
00:59:52,560 --> 00:59:54,760
I'm just going to buy some supplies
for the pharmacy before I go.

907
00:59:55,630 --> 00:59:57,130
By the way, about this laptop...

908
00:59:57,700 --> 00:59:59,330
Aunt used this sometimes too, right?

909
00:59:59,700 --> 01:00:02,500
Yes, she did. Why?

910
01:00:02,640 --> 01:00:05,510
It's automatically logged in
to a web portal with her email.

911
01:00:06,010 --> 01:00:07,010
- What?
- What?

912
01:00:09,980 --> 01:00:13,650
I thought it was my account,
but it has a new order and address.

913
01:00:27,600 --> 01:00:29,530
Wait, Cabanel?

914
01:00:30,260 --> 01:00:33,400
Cabanel. It's Cabanel.
Cabanel... Stepmom.

915
01:00:35,640 --> 01:00:37,440
Stepmom!

916
01:00:38,540 --> 01:00:40,980
- The Cabanel bag's been listed.
- What?

917
01:00:41,010 --> 01:00:44,580
I think Uncle listed it
on a resale app to sell it!

918
01:00:45,380 --> 01:00:49,280
- Really?
- Yes, really! Where's Aunt?

919
01:00:50,590 --> 01:00:51,820
Excuse me, Chief.

920
01:00:53,450 --> 01:00:57,860
By any chance, can you do location
or vehicle tracking?

921
01:00:57,930 --> 01:00:59,390
(Warm and Reliable Police)

922
01:00:59,460 --> 01:01:03,870
That's a hot request these days.
Location and vehicle tracking.

923
01:01:05,630 --> 01:01:07,270
Is this about a family member?

924
01:01:07,800 --> 01:01:11,970
If you file a missing person report,
we can help you with that.

925
01:01:12,570 --> 01:01:13,640
No, it's not like that.

926
01:01:14,940 --> 01:01:18,380
I couldn't just sit around,
so I thought I'd come and ask.

927
01:01:19,480 --> 01:01:20,850
- I see.
- Right.

928
01:01:28,220 --> 01:01:29,360
Excuse me.

929
01:01:29,520 --> 01:01:33,060
Can't you just run the license plate
through the system?

930
01:01:34,500 --> 01:01:36,830
- Can't you do it for me?
- I can't do that.

931
01:01:41,170 --> 01:01:43,170
- Please, sir. I'm begging you.
- What?

932
01:01:43,500 --> 01:01:48,080
Can't you just find out where he is?
The plate is 314 J9542.

933
01:01:48,340 --> 01:01:50,080
- I can't.
- Wait, 314 J9542?

934
01:01:50,140 --> 01:01:52,280
- Chief, please. Just this once.
- We can't.

935
01:01:52,350 --> 01:01:57,220
- Chief, please. Just once...
- Auntie! I know where Uncle is!

936
01:01:57,390 --> 01:02:01,090
- What?
- That Cabanel bag! For real! Hurry!

937
01:02:01,790 --> 01:02:03,390
- Where is he?
- Quick!

938
01:02:03,460 --> 01:02:06,430
- Chief?
- What?

939
01:02:06,960 --> 01:02:08,100
The person
that lady is looking for...

940
01:02:08,630 --> 01:02:09,700
I think it's this guy.

941
01:02:11,570 --> 01:02:12,570
What?

942
01:02:18,740 --> 01:02:20,980
Mom, I think that's the place.

943
01:02:25,110 --> 01:02:27,950
(Hui Gyeong Hair Salon)

944
01:02:34,960 --> 01:02:36,360
(Hui Gyeong Hair Salon)

945
01:02:37,360 --> 01:02:38,890
Hurry up and come out, honey.

946
01:02:41,960 --> 01:02:43,000
That's Hui Gyeong.

947
01:02:46,870 --> 01:02:48,540
Honey, just a second.

948
01:02:49,500 --> 01:02:51,470
(Hui Gyeong Hair Salon)

949
01:02:51,610 --> 01:02:53,310
Hey, that guy.

950
01:02:54,910 --> 01:02:57,210
Oh, my. Wait.

951
01:02:57,680 --> 01:02:59,280
Isn't he the son-in-law
from the Korean medicine clinic?

952
01:03:00,210 --> 01:03:01,220
No way.

953
01:03:01,780 --> 01:03:03,650
- Honey, wait just a second.
- Okay.

954
01:03:05,520 --> 01:03:07,290
- Mom, Grandma.
- I can't believe it.

955
01:03:07,890 --> 01:03:08,890
What is it?

956
01:03:10,090 --> 01:03:11,090
Look.

957
01:03:14,860 --> 01:03:17,270
- This is it, right?
- Dong Suk, over here!

958
01:03:20,130 --> 01:03:22,970
- What now?
- If you go this way...

959
01:03:23,440 --> 01:03:24,440
It's close by.

960
01:03:52,530 --> 01:03:55,370
(Recipe For Love)

961
01:03:56,270 --> 01:03:57,510
Are you protesting or something?

962
01:03:58,370 --> 01:04:01,780
- Gong Ju Ah and I are just friends.
- Friends?

963
01:04:01,840 --> 01:04:02,840
We're old friends.

964
01:04:02,910 --> 01:04:05,410
Then why the long face?
Are you sure you're just friends?

965
01:04:05,480 --> 01:04:07,110
Men and women can't be just friends.

966
01:04:07,220 --> 01:04:08,220
Well...

967
01:04:08,550 --> 01:04:10,120
What about my place?

968
01:04:10,450 --> 01:04:14,460
But apparently, their parents
have also been my patients.

969
01:04:14,720 --> 01:04:15,760
I wonder who they are.

970
01:04:15,760 --> 01:04:17,690
How about a blind date
with my brother?

971
01:04:18,630 --> 01:04:19,730
A blind date?

972
01:04:20,460 --> 01:04:22,800
We truly love each other.

973
01:04:22,800 --> 01:04:25,070
Loving someone's no crime, is it?

974
01:04:25,070 --> 01:04:26,070
Hey!
